Cisco IOS-XE operational state data (read-only).
**Category:** Other Services
**Paths:** 13

**YANG Model:** [Cisco-IOS-XE-l2tp-oper.yang](https://github.com/YangModels/yang/blob/main/vendor/cisco/xe/17181/Cisco-IOS-XE-l2tp-oper.yang)

**📊 YANG Tree:** [View Cisco-IOS-XE-l2tp-oper structure](https://jeremycohoe.github.io/cisco-ios-xe-openapi-swagger/yang-trees/Cisco-IOS-XE-l2tp-oper.html)

local-ip-address.description: Tunnel local end point IP address[ipv4/ipv6]

remote-ip-address.description: Tunnel remote end point IP address [ipv4/ipv6]

l2tp-class-name.description: L2TP class name for the tunnel

is-path-mtu-enabled.description: True if path MTU is set

last-state-change-time.description: Time since the last state change occurred

total-resend.description: Total number of packets were resend

out-of-order-drops.description: Total number of out of order packets were dropped

out-of-order-reorder.description: Total number of out of order packets were reordered

congestion-ctrl-avoid-pkts.description: Packets count in congestion avoidance mode

count-since-clear.description: Packet counters by taking last clear into account

count-ignore-clear.description: Packet counters ignoring the last clear

number-of-digests.description:
Control message authentication is enabled with
         how many digest secrets

slow-start-threshold.description:
Threshold limit.The point at which the sending device
         switches operation from slow start mode to
         congestion avoidance mode

is-local-window-size-default.description: True if local window size is default

is-max-remote-window-size.description: True if maximum remote window size is set

is-locally-initiated.description:
True if the tunnel was locally initiated or
         False if the tunnel was initiated by the remote end

is-congestion-ctrl-slow-start.description: True if congestion control mode is slow start

is-congestion-ctrl-enabled.description: True if congestion control is enabled

using-digest-secret2.description: True if control message authentication is enabled

is-incomplete-export.description: True if unable to export the data

queue-check-attempts.description:
Number of times packet queue check is hit,
         before shutting down the tunnel. This delays tunnel shut down,
         if control channel has outstanding packets.

max-queue-check-attempts.description: Maximum number of attempts allowed to check packet queue
